jeudi 24 avril 2025

On the Road with Jennifer K Dick, Bremner Fletcher and Lisa Pasold le 30 avril à Paris



INVITATION A UNE SOIREE DE POESIE ET MUSIQUE EN ANGLAIS / INVITATION TO AN EVENING OF POETRY AND MUSIC IN ENGLISH WITH

JENNIFER K DICK
BREMNER FLETCHER &
LISA PASOLD

 

30 avril 2025 à 19h30

à :   Delaville Café, au 1er étage, 34 boulevard Bonne Nouvelle,

75010 Paris M° Bonne nouvelle (ligne 8 or 9)

RDv au bar for drinks, then head upstairs!

BIOS:

Jennifer K Dick is the author of the books That Which I Touch Has No Name (Black Spring Press Group, London, 2022) & Lilith: a Novel in Fragments (Corrupt, 2019), Circuits (Corrupt 2013) & Fluorescence (U GA, 2004) as well as 7 chap/artbooks, most recently Meridian (Estepa Editions, France, 2023). Jennifer has been increasingly interested in the ways collaboration, cross-genre exploration & collage can inform her & other's art, & has participated in films, dance-poetry projects & had an installation of her writing on a building at the SBB Basel. Jennifer runs Ivy Writers Paris reading series & co-directs Ecrire l'Art residency at the Kunsthalle Mulhouse Centre d'Art Contemporain.

Originally from Montréal, Lisa Pasold is the author of six books. Her chapbook Kindnesses is upcoming this year with Cactus Press. She is a performer, storyteller & poet. Her 2012 poetic narrative, Any Bright Horse was shortlisted for Canada’s Governor General’s Award. Lisa has taught at the Paris Writers Workshop & the American University in Paris. She is currently touring with New Orleans singer Bremner Fletcher, performing texts she has written. For more, see: https://www.lisapasold.com/ 

Bremner Fletcher has made his career performing & recording songs he loves, from John Cage to Leonard Cohen and with a special focus on Weill and Brecht. He has performed with jazz bands, chamber ensembles and orchestras, & has sung avant-garde works from the 20th Century. Bremner is now spotlighting his own songwriting, using his years of experience interpreting those brilliant writers to write and sing his own songs. Listen to a sample here:
